opments in new materialism by exploring the intersections among bodies, material elements, social arrangements, and discourses through body and flesh. By painting a complex picture of bodies, and by developing an account of how the social materializes in flesh, Rivera provides a new way to understand gender and race.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aChristian philosophy. 0aFlesh (Theology) 0aFlesh (Theology). 0aHuman body (Philosophy) 0aHuman body (Philosophy). 0aHuman bodyxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 7aRELIGION / Theology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374930zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374930423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374930.jpg  a978-3-11-071182-0  DUK eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles